Contagious bovine pleuropneumonia, Zambia
----------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 21 Apr 2017 from Dr Yona Sinkala, Director, Department of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Fisheries and Livestock, Lusaka, Zambia

Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 6 Apr 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 18 Apr 2017
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: Jan 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Mycoplasma mycoides_ subsp. _mycoides_ SC (bovine biotype)
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Makononga Village, Kazungula Central Veterinary Camp, Kazungula, Southern
Date of start of the outbreak: 6 Apr 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 724 / 3 / 2 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The affected population of cattle is a local beef breed comprising of animals above 12 months old under traditional management system.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.41 / 0.28 / 66.67 / 0.28
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals.
Epidemiological comments: Kazungula District has not reported any cases of CBPP since 2009. Animals in the area are not vaccinated against the disease. A policy of testing and slaughtering any positive animal is in place.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, vaccination prohibited, no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: screening, traceability, surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone, modified stamping out.

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result
Central Veterinary Research Institute (National laboratory)/ Cattle/ competitive ELISA (c-ELISA)/ 18 Apr 2017/ Positive
Central Veterinary Research Institute (National laboratory)/ Cattle/ pathogen isolation on cell culture/ 18 Apr 2017/ Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

